# Example App Standards (Ant Design)

## Critical Rules
- Use Ant Design components for the example/demo app UI
- Follow Ant Design design patterns and conventions
- Use Layout, Tabs, and other Ant Design components appropriately
- Maintain clean separation between library code and example code
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces with Ant Design component props
- Organize example sections logically with clear navigation

## Ant Design Patterns
- Use Layout components (Header, Content, Sider) for page structure
- Use Tabs for section navigation
- Use proper styling with Ant Design's style props
- Combine Ant Design with custom styling when needed for demos

## Examples

<example>
```tsx
// Example app using Ant Design properly
import { Layout, Tabs } from 'antd';
import { CustomCursor } from '@yhattav/react-component-cursor';

const { Content, Header } = Layout;
const { TabPane } = Tabs;

function App() {
  const [activeSection, setActiveSection] = useState('demo');

  return (
    <Layout style={{ height: '100vh' }}>
      <Header style={{ background: '#fff', padding: '0 16px' }}>
        <Tabs activeKey={activeSection} onChange={setActiveSection}>
          <TabPane tab="Demo" key="demo" />
          <TabPane tab="Advanced" key="advanced" />
        </Tabs>
      </Header>
      <Content style={{ position: 'relative', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
        <CustomCursor>
          <div style={{
            width: '20px',
            height: '20px',
            backgroundColor: '#1890ff',
            borderRadius: '50%',
            transform: 'translate(-50%, -50%)',
          }} />
        </CustomCursor>
        {/* Demo content */}
      </Content>
    </Layout>
  );
}
```
</example>

